  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut narrow slices (about 1cm apart) into the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base – these are your<strong> hasselback sweet potatoes</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>hasselback sweet potatoes </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656060674290-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656060674290-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656060674290-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656060674290-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656060674290-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover the tray tightly with <strong>tin foil </strong>and put in the oven for an initial 45 min</p><p>After 45 min, remove the tray from the oven, remove the tin foil and drizzle over the <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Return the tray to the oven, uncovered, for 10 min further or until the potatoes are soft and caramelised – this is your <strong>harissa & honey hasselback sweet potato</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656060690060-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656060690060-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656060690060-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656060690060-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656060690060-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1656060705694-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
